00:36:48,619 --> 00:36:49,980
Inge raised the question.

481
00:36:54,360 --> 00:36:59,719
It's indeed a bid on the part of the angels to become the representative, did you not

482
00:36:59,719 --> 00:37:00,179
suggest it?

483
00:37:01,119 --> 00:37:02,300
No, you mentioned the word, "representative."

484
00:37:02,659 --> 00:37:05,480
And then I wanted to know why they would do that, you know, this thing of wanting to

485
00:37:05,480 --> 00:37:06,280
supplant him for God.

486
00:37:06,280 --> 00:37:14,659
Many people, many persons have interpreted this verse to mean that the angels are saying

487
00:37:14,659 --> 00:37:17,920
to God, "Why put people who shed blood?"

488
00:37:17,920 --> 00:37:24,679
I think they were making a deal, the angels wanted to be the representatives.

489
00:37:25,079 --> 00:37:30,539
Some people have asked this question, and I've heard it, and it's very curious that Inge suggested that, no?

490
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:34,280
I wanted to ask, were they offering that, or was it something to do with jealousy?

491
00:37:34,619 --> 00:37:36,079
Well, rather than the jealousy.

492
00:37:36,099 --> 00:37:39,000
It's a simple question. It's a simple question.

493
00:37:39,519 --> 00:37:42,000
Why create a creature who will defy and revolt?

494
00:37:42,619 --> 00:37:43,880
We do not do that.

495
00:37:44,780 --> 00:37:47,460
It's an excellent question. If I said I knew what it is...

496
00:37:47,460 --> 00:37:53,460
But isn't this a deal on the part of the angels, that they're asking for something in exchange?

497
00:37:53,880 --> 00:37:57,000
They're already much higher.

498
00:37:57,239 --> 00:37:58,440
It's a very interesting question.

499
00:37:58,599 --> 00:37:59,760
They do not want to be lower.

500
00:38:01,679 --> 00:38:06,980
When God said "representative on earth," that's a terrible demotion.

501
00:38:07,760 --> 00:38:12,820
And that's exactly what tipped off the angels as to the nature of the human being.

502
00:38:14,119 --> 00:38:21,059
Shedding blood, corrupting the earth, not praising God when he should be praised.

503
00:38:21,619 --> 00:38:24,099
And the evidence was all around us.

504
00:38:28,480 --> 00:38:34,900
It is because there are those names, when people look at angels, some names that you are aware of.

505
00:38:36,980 --> 00:38:42,820
I just talked about this thing a couple of times before, and I'm not comfortable with it.

506
00:38:42,920 --> 00:38:43,260
I don't...

507
00:38:43,860 --> 00:38:45,400
Well, how, let me put it this way.

508
00:38:45,619 --> 00:38:47,079
Who was it that was presented to the angels?

509
00:38:48,960 --> 00:38:52,179
Adam, Adam, Adam, Adam, Adam, Adam, Adam, Adam, Adam, Adam, Adam, Adam.

510
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:56,320
Right. Did you watch the funeral of Princess Grace?

511
00:38:58,159 --> 00:39:01,579
Well, we did. It was here on the TV, right?

512
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:05,820
So there's an event going on, on the other side of the globe,

513
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:07,719
that we're watching live here.

514
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:11,500
Everything that's happening over there, we're watching it here.

515
00:39:11,760 --> 00:39:16,420
And how do you think the angels feel about this invention of the TV?

516
00:39:19,219 --> 00:39:21,699
Now this is the kind of thing that God taught us.

517
00:39:23,280 --> 00:39:27,119
When a person is sitting in Washington D.C., I was sitting in Tucson.

518
00:39:28,599 --> 00:39:29,659
That's quite an event.

519
00:39:33,739 --> 00:39:37,860
Now, so, this is the kind of knowledge that amazed the angels.

520
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:41,099
This was meant by the names.

521
00:39:41,099 --> 00:39:45,199
In other words, God gave a human being knowledge.

522
00:39:46,660 --> 00:39:56,199
How do you think the angels feel about a 747 flying, a huge city, floating in the air?

523
00:39:57,800 --> 00:39:59,179
Did you ride a 747?

524
00:40:01,960 --> 00:40:04,579
Did you ride a 747 plane?

525
00:40:05,400 --> 00:40:11,659
When you ride it, you look inside and you just wonder how is this steel, this thing

526
00:40:11,659 --> 00:40:17,360
built of steel, and aluminum, etc., etc., and carpets, and engines, and so forth, is up

527
00:40:17,360 --> 00:40:18,340
floating in the air.

528
00:40:18,900 --> 00:40:24,139
And when you sit at the, you go to the other end of the plane and look inside, it's a whole

529
00:40:24,139 --> 00:40:25,900
like a floating city.

530
00:40:26,219 --> 00:40:32,800
And the human being did that, and the angels watching in amazement.

531
00:40:34,599 --> 00:40:39,199
So this is the, this is the knowledge that God gave to the human being.

532
00:40:41,960 --> 00:40:49,619
Inventing the TV, the video recorder, the airplane, that's what's meant by the names.

533
00:40:51,800 --> 00:40:54,079
So that really explains what you wanted to say.

534
00:40:55,099 --> 00:40:55,619
Right.

535
00:40:57,240 --> 00:40:57,900
Thank you.

536
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:00,739
Question over there?

537
00:41:01,260 --> 00:41:01,780
Yes.

538
00:41:04,699 --> 00:41:06,639
What did he make the soul out of?

539
00:41:07,039 --> 00:41:09,800
Yes, that's the question in Surah 17.

540
00:41:10,460 --> 00:41:12,260
What did he make the soul out of?

541
00:41:16,239 --> 00:41:18,639
That you find out in a different dimension.

542
00:41:20,380 --> 00:41:21,280
That's the answer.

543
00:41:24,500 --> 00:41:26,280
The soul is in a different dimension.

544
00:41:28,599 --> 00:41:30,719
But the soul is part of God, by the way.

545
00:41:35,259 --> 00:41:42,980
Great, good. The soul is a small part of God, which is why when you do things that have to do with God, your soul grows.

546
00:41:44,519 --> 00:41:48,059
What this soul looks like, what it is made of, you will find out in the day of resurrection.

547
00:41:50,019 --> 00:41:52,679
Now that's not symmetrical, is it? Okay, go ahead.

548
00:42:04,380 --> 00:42:10,480
Okay, so that was the first purpose of creating the human being, is to expose Satan.

549
00:42:10,880 --> 00:42:14,519
Because God made him up out of clay, of lowly material.

550
00:42:16,380 --> 00:42:19,099
And Satan was very, very arrogant and rebellious.

551
00:42:20,199 --> 00:42:24,599
So God told the angels, this is what God knew, that the angels would not disobey.

552
00:42:25,900 --> 00:42:26,380
Alright.

553
00:42:26,960 --> 00:42:27,360
Thank you.

554
00:42:27,579 --> 00:42:28,960
I'm sorry.

555
00:42:29,400 --> 00:42:30,380
Give me your question again.

556
00:42:31,920 --> 00:42:39,300
When Satan was cast out, was any other angel cast out with him or not?

557
00:42:39,400 --> 00:42:41,719
He was just cast out, and we are not told of any other.

558
00:42:45,420 --> 00:42:48,019
God has made a deal with him for a time.

559
00:42:50,679 --> 00:42:56,440
What does the Bible say? I think the Bible mentions other angels who work with him.

560
00:43:12,740 --> 00:43:15,960
What's the question again?

561
00:43:16,440 --> 00:43:19,539
The question is, was Satan cast out alone or did he have entities with him?

562
00:43:20,780 --> 00:43:21,780
Fallen entities.

563
00:43:21,780 --> 00:43:32,340
In the Bible, not in the Torah, not in the Psalms, but in other parts of the Bible, a big group went with him.

564
00:43:34,400 --> 00:43:36,219
It doesn't matter though, that's the...

565
00:43:36,219 --> 00:43:40,639
When I was wondering what it was like back then, was Satan tempted by Satan?

566
00:43:41,639 --> 00:43:42,159
Yeah.

567
00:43:42,519 --> 00:43:44,179
I was wondering what, you know...

568
00:43:44,179 --> 00:43:48,699
We were not, we were not with Adam at the time either.

569
00:43:48,699 --> 00:43:56,179
We didn't exist. We are descendants of Adam, but we didn't exist then, I mean our bodies.

570
00:44:01,119 --> 00:44:06,119
Descendants means they came from him, not that all descendants were with him.

571
00:44:08,260 --> 00:44:12,400
But I can't think of any place in Quran where it mentions any other angels.

572
00:44:12,400 --> 00:44:14,820
Iblis was just cast out by himself.

573
00:44:18,219 --> 00:44:18,619
Yes.

574
00:44:19,299 --> 00:44:23,699
I thought it was said that Adam was made from clay,

575
00:44:23,739 --> 00:44:28,420
and angels from light,

576
00:44:28,900 --> 00:44:30,579
and the jinn were made from fire?

577
00:44:31,239 --> 00:44:32,440
They were made out of the fire.

578
00:44:33,019 --> 00:44:35,199
The angels were made out of fire, not made out of light.

579
00:44:39,780 --> 00:44:44,199
The definition of jinn, the definition of jinn is a hidden angel.

580
00:44:45,559 --> 00:44:48,659
So the angel, when the angel rebels, becomes a jinn.

581
00:44:50,579 --> 00:44:54,559
When Satan became a jinn, he was an angel.

582
00:44:57,720 --> 00:45:11,760
Some of the old sheikhs decided that Satan was not an angel; I think it's lack of knowledge

583
00:45:11,760 --> 00:45:17,940
of the Arabic language. This happens only in Persia and Pakistan, where they refute

584
00:45:17,940 --> 00:45:19,739
that Satan was an angel.

585
00:45:19,739 --> 00:45:22,579
But if you look, do you have a copy of the Quran there?

586
00:45:23,119 --> 00:45:26,940
If you look at this, verse 34, it says,

587
00:45:27,039 --> 00:45:30,559
And We said to the angels,

588
00:45:32,119 --> 00:45:35,460
fall prostrate before Adam. So, it's certain.

589
00:45:36,199 --> 00:45:39,599
If Satan were not an angel, he would not be required to

590
00:45:39,599 --> 00:45:42,360
prostrate. He, therefore, broke God's law.

591
00:45:43,300 --> 00:45:45,639
Because God told the angels to prostrate.

592
00:45:48,239 --> 00:45:51,300
Right? There is absolutely no question that Satan was one of them.

593
00:45:53,920 --> 00:45:56,400
I've heard all of these stories, but they don't mean anything.

594
00:45:57,059 --> 00:45:57,519
What?

595
00:45:57,780 --> 00:46:02,179
When I was listening to a scholar, for instance, I heard an old statement saying he was blind.

596
00:46:02,380 --> 00:46:05,920
It's a hadith. The Quran doesn't say that he was blind.

597
00:46:06,119 --> 00:46:07,960
But it says that these additions are made in contrast.

598
00:46:08,179 --> 00:46:08,440
Right.

599
00:46:14,599 --> 00:46:21,719
The jinn were made of fire, so since a jinn was an angel initially, then I suppose

600
00:46:21,719 --> 00:46:23,079
the angels were made of fire.

601
00:46:23,400 --> 00:46:24,639
We have the same theory.

602
00:46:33,199 --> 00:46:35,940
But there's no difference between fire and light.

603
00:46:35,940 --> 00:46:38,679
Anyway, the angels made of light is a hadith.

604
00:46:39,480 --> 00:46:40,139
The ruh.

605
00:46:42,119 --> 00:46:43,000
What's the question?

606
00:46:44,760 --> 00:46:46,800
Now, there is the second question.

607
00:46:47,420 --> 00:46:48,199
What word?

608
00:46:48,820 --> 00:46:51,340
The word that we see, the word that is pure.

609
00:46:52,579 --> 00:46:54,519
And what does He say?

610
00:46:56,199 --> 00:46:58,880
When We said to the angels, "Bow down to Adam,"

611
00:46:59,079 --> 00:47:01,760
they bowed down, except Iblis.

612
00:47:01,760 --> 00:47:06,019
He said, "Shall I bow down to one whom You created from clay?"

613
00:47:06,679 --> 00:47:11,480
So what I understand from this is that Adam was only created in a form.

614
00:47:11,719 --> 00:47:13,179
It's his bodily form there.

615
00:47:13,780 --> 00:47:16,920
So they could see the clay form of his body.

616
00:47:17,420 --> 00:47:23,159
But later on it says that when he ate from the tree, his body became visible to them.

617
00:47:24,039 --> 00:47:25,659
So it sounds like...

618
00:47:25,659 --> 00:47:27,559
Do you see a soul?

619
00:47:29,300 --> 00:47:29,840
No.

620
00:47:29,840 --> 00:47:36,739
The soul is ruh. The ruh is not visible. But you are now in the dimension where the body is visible to you.

621
00:47:37,619 --> 00:47:42,219
You are not in the dimension of the ruh, the soul. This is why you don't see it.

622
00:47:42,500 --> 00:47:49,760
So, before eating from the tree, they were in the dimension of the soul, where the body is invisible to them.

623
00:47:50,519 --> 00:47:59,820
And as soon as they broke God's law, they went down to the dimension where the body is visible to them.

624
00:48:02,779 --> 00:48:04,960
You cannot be in there, in both of them.

625
00:48:09,820 --> 00:48:13,360
Yes, it's very clear in the Quran that when they ate from the tree, their bodies became

626
00:48:13,360 --> 00:48:14,179
visible to them.

627
00:48:15,579 --> 00:48:19,019
But the angels could see, of course, they have to see both of them.

628
00:48:19,199 --> 00:48:20,519
And they are God's helpers.

629
00:48:21,300 --> 00:48:24,139
They are supposed to have access to any body.

630
00:48:26,519 --> 00:48:27,300
Other questions?

631
00:48:30,200 --> 00:48:34,599
First, I think we're going into it too far.

632
00:48:36,820 --> 00:48:44,699
This idea of the names, maybe we should spend some more time on it.

633
00:48:45,480 --> 00:48:47,699
Basically, we compare it with the...

634
00:48:48,300 --> 00:48:50,719
We're not studying the Bible of the Jews and Christians,

635
00:48:52,099 --> 00:48:57,679
but I think if we go deeper, we might learn something, maybe.

636
00:48:58,420 --> 00:49:01,079
For example, one difference is this.

637
00:49:01,219 --> 00:49:10,300
In the Bible of the Jews and Christians, it does not say that God taught Adam.

638
00:49:17,080 --> 00:49:27,880
There, Adam, on his own accord, began to give names to the animals and the plants.

639
00:49:29,659 --> 00:49:30,840
This is already one difference.

640
00:49:31,360 --> 00:49:36,780
In the Quran, Allah teaches Adam the names, whatever these names are.

641
00:49:36,780 --> 00:49:40,800
But in the Bible of the Jews, Adam is on his own.

642
00:49:42,460 --> 00:49:44,699
There's no suggestion that Allah teaches Adam.

643
00:49:44,920 --> 00:49:50,860
It's Adam who goes to the garden and he starts to name the things that God created.

644
00:49:51,199 --> 00:49:53,340
I think this is very important.

645
00:49:53,860 --> 00:49:58,360
Because the way Moses Maimonides, who is the greatest Jewish philosopher,

646
00:49:58,619 --> 00:50:04,420
describes how Adam is naming animals and plants,

647
00:50:04,420 --> 00:50:08,679
you would think that Adam was a professor of botany and zoology.

648
00:50:10,420 --> 00:50:17,380
And I would think that Adam would have bigger things to worry about.

649
00:50:18,580 --> 00:50:26,019
So, many Muslims in their tafsir, guided by the readings of the Jewish Bible,

650
00:50:26,179 --> 00:50:31,599
and to demonstrate to other Muslims that they know something else beyond the Quran,

651
00:50:31,599 --> 00:50:41,420
Theologians began to teach us that what Allah taught Adam were the names of animals and plants.

652
00:50:41,860 --> 00:50:46,719
So this time, it's Allah who becomes the professor of botany and zoology.

653
00:50:48,599 --> 00:50:55,300
Now, it seems there is something in the names which the angels do not know, or maybe cannot know.

654
00:50:56,360 --> 00:50:57,739
But they can know some.

655
00:50:57,739 --> 00:51:09,119
Now, this is very interesting, there have been many interpretations about this, of many kinds, some tolerant and some indulgent.

656
00:51:10,740 --> 00:51:20,659
There is a standard teaching among some Sufi writers, that these names refer to the names of Allah.

657
00:51:21,800 --> 00:51:30,159
Now, first of all, I think among the Arabs, knowing a name is more than knowing a name,

658
00:51:30,239 --> 00:51:30,860
like, say, sir.

659
00:51:31,139 --> 00:51:31,500
No.

660
00:51:31,739 --> 00:51:37,659
As Ustaz is saying, a name refers to more than the name of someone, it refers to knowledge,

661
00:51:37,860 --> 00:51:39,039
which I accept.

662
00:51:39,139 --> 00:51:39,599
You mentioned it.

663
00:51:41,119 --> 00:51:47,340
And most people who have made commentary will agree that these names refer to knowledge.

664
00:51:47,340 --> 00:51:55,360
Knowledge. Some say knowledge of abstraction. That is the intelligence of man. He can go

665
00:51:55,360 --> 00:52:02,960
from the concrete to the abstract. He can go and rationalize or reason, we say.

666
00:52:03,239 --> 00:52:10,360
In other words, he can know logic. But I am very much inclined to accept the hints of

667
00:52:10,360 --> 00:52:19,739
the Sufis when they say that Allah taught Adam the names of His qualities.

668
00:52:21,159 --> 00:52:26,119
Now this is knowledge of the highest form. And the angels cannot know all. For example,

669
00:52:27,380 --> 00:52:33,420
Allah, one of the names of Allah is, He is One who gives death. Now angels, it seems,

670
00:52:33,420 --> 00:52:34,460
don't know what is death.

671
00:52:36,619 --> 00:52:37,219
Death.

672
00:52:38,220 --> 00:52:39,260
Allah who willed

673
00:52:39,260 --> 00:52:39,780
it.

674
00:52:41,380 --> 00:52:42,820
But Adam can understand

675
00:52:43,420 --> 00:52:44,500
eventually the meaning of death.

676
00:52:45,039 --> 00:52:45,880
Another thing.

677
00:52:46,800 --> 00:52:49,420
An angel, as philosophers

678
00:52:49,420 --> 00:52:51,099
argue, cannot understand

679
00:52:51,099 --> 00:52:52,860
the meaning of

680
00:52:53,420 --> 00:52:55,280
patience or the care of children.

681
00:52:55,639 --> 00:52:56,219
You know.

682
00:52:56,760 --> 00:52:58,119
Because they don't have children.

683
00:52:59,420 --> 00:53:00,840
So when Allah tells us to be patient,

684
00:53:00,840 --> 00:53:05,480
we understand that. If Allah helps us, we understand Allah if He tells us to be patient.

685
00:53:05,800 --> 00:53:11,179
This is a quality which Allah helps us develop. But the angels cannot have this.

686
00:53:11,599 --> 00:53:17,539
In other words, the angels belonging to another dimension and not having a physical body like us

687
00:53:17,539 --> 00:53:25,679
cannot exemplify some of the virtues which Allah already wants us to demonstrate.

688
00:53:26,460 --> 00:53:36,559
And I think many of these names of Allah, like for example Al-Musawwir, and also Allah

689
00:53:36,559 --> 00:53:39,039
is Al-Muhyi, He who gives life.

690
00:53:39,300 --> 00:53:41,480
In some ways we do give life with the help of Allah.

691
00:53:41,659 --> 00:53:47,619
When we have children, we are in some ways creating, naturally with the help of Allah,

692
00:53:47,800 --> 00:53:48,860
we are creating lives.

693
00:53:49,659 --> 00:53:53,539
And I do not think angels understand that.

694
00:53:53,539 --> 00:53:55,719
They cannot know this thing.

695
00:53:55,900 --> 00:53:57,599
Be careful now, don't make them angry.

696
00:53:58,759 --> 00:54:00,280
No, because I cannot see them.

697
00:54:00,320 --> 00:54:01,059
They're watching you now.

698
00:54:02,579 --> 00:54:05,760
I'm talking to you because I cannot show you with my eyes.

699
00:54:06,099 --> 00:54:11,119
So, maybe I'll be borne out with my eyes.

700
00:54:11,159 --> 00:54:13,820
Watch what you say about the angels because you don't want to make them angry.

701
00:54:17,400 --> 00:54:24,699
And so, the way I look at it is that I agree that these names refer to knowledge, and I

702
00:54:24,699 --> 00:54:29,420
would just like to submit for your thinking, for you to develop on your own, or reject,

703
00:54:29,699 --> 00:54:34,119
that maybe these names are a special form of knowledge.

704
00:54:34,280 --> 00:54:41,980
They refer to those special qualities of Allah which He gave us the ability to exercise when

705
00:54:41,980 --> 00:54:47,480
He, as we just mentioned, gave part of himself to us as a soul.

706
00:54:47,659 --> 00:54:52,400
He breathed unto us something of his spirit.

707
00:54:52,619 --> 00:54:53,480
That is our soul.

708
00:54:53,800 --> 00:54:57,480
And this gives us the capacity to understand certain things.

709
00:54:57,639 --> 00:55:00,639
And the angels can never know this.

710
00:55:00,820 --> 00:55:06,980
It seems to me, therefore, that in our test in life, you need a body.

711
00:55:09,119 --> 00:55:14,360
And you need the combination of this body with part of ourselves, which really is Allah's,

712
00:55:14,460 --> 00:55:18,139
to exercise certain things in order to arrive at certain knowledge.

713
00:55:18,500 --> 00:55:22,860
And this is what Allah has given us.

714
00:55:23,019 --> 00:55:24,980
And that's why He has sent us to a material world,

715
00:55:25,119 --> 00:55:29,719
